<section>
  <h2>Welcome</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>River Runner</strong> is a community-powered data collection tool for monitoring river health.
    This version uses <a href="https://survey123.arcgis.com/" target="_blank">Survey123</a> to allow rapid reporting of issues like:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Erosion</li>
    <li>Invasive Species</li>
    <li>Dumping and Debris</li>
    <li>Unusual Water Conditions</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Observations are submitted through a mobile-friendly survey and stored in an ArcGIS Feature Layer.
    You can <strong>start collecting right now</strong> using a phone or browser.
  </p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Project Goals</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Enable fast and accessible field reporting</li>
    <li>Support data-driven outreach and advocacy</li>
    <li>Serve as a prototype for a future standalone Flutter app</li>
  </ul>
</section>
